93.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  hmm</span><hr size=1> Way i see it they arent adding anything extra zone wise which is a bit sloppy really. They are basically stealing the whole character development system from DAoC. They are also stealing the system of people having equipment to high for their lvl from DAoC. <br>
<br>
Now daoc was fun but really wasnt that great IMO. the character development system wasnt especially well tweaked to the right level and the equipment system had alot of silly flaws which often meant you were wearing stuff way to low for your level etc.<br>
<br>
These and other reasons are why DAoC hasnt made as much of a dent into eq as was originally expected.<br>
<br>
Verant being verant they will steal these systems and then totally screw them up to make them &quot;their own&quot;. They really dont seem to have learnt alot from eq at all so i seriously doubt you'll see any better quality of programming in EQ2. you'll still have the usual bugs exploits and massive downtime.<br>
<br>
Also marketing wise its probably one of the stupidist things they could do to make everyone start over. I think a while back they stated they have one million accounts active at the moment. You are turning round and telling one million accounts ok you worked hard and leveled up etc etc but we dont give a poo you are gonna have to start again under a totally different system. that stands to probably annoy a fair few people.<br>
<br>
Lets face it if they REALLY wanted to they could take the current world, and better spend their time by recreating the world under their new engine, up the level cap some maybe or expand the higher end things like AAXP, throw in some new skills for the lower/middle levels and have it so that we can actually take the characters we have now into the new world.<br>
then package it up. Ship it out with all expansions under new engine too and charge the usual arm and a leg for it.<br>
<br>
It can be done and it'd keep people alot happier and enable you to have a new engine, new zones, and new mecahnics.<br>
<br>
Hell they could even totally change zones if you wanted more unexplored content. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvittoriotalamasca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vittorio Talamasca</A> at: 4/28/02 2:09:56 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=11493.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=11493.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11493.topic&index=27><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~eqmaximus/brell/addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.threadControl?topicID=11493.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11493.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11493.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm70">News and Events<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm58">The Outer Real